<section xml:id="second-derivatives-and-applications">
<title>Second derivatives and applications</title>


<paragraphs xml:id="the-plan-13">
<title>The Plan</title>

<p> Given our work on the mechanics of computing
derivatives, we will focus on the interpretation and application of
derivatives.<!-- linebreak -->
</p>


<paragraphs xml:id="first-second-derivatives">
<title>Derivatives</title>

<p>	When discussing functions and derivatives, <em>the
derivative</em> of a function refers to its first derivative. Since
derivatives of functions are functions too, we can take <sq>higher
derivatives</sq> using our current methods. Perhaps the most common
higher derivative is the second derivative.
</p>


