<p> Concavity describes the shape of a graph.
</p>

<p><ul>
<li> <p> a graph of <m>f(x)</m> is <term>concave
up</term> if it <sq>bends upward,</sq><!-- linebreak -->
</p>

<p><ul>
<li> <p> if its first derivative is increasing, or</p> </li>
<li> <p> if <m>f''(x)&gt;0</m> (the second derivative is
positive)</p> </li>

</ul></p> </li>

<li> <p> a graph of <m>f(x)</m> is <term>concave
down</term> if it <sq>bends downward,</sq><!-- linebreak -->
</p>

<p><ul>
<li> <p> if its first derivative is decreasing, or</p> </li>
<li> <p> if <m>f''(x)&lt;0</m> (the second derivative is
negative)</p> </li>

</ul></p> </li>

</ul></p>

